(10, 'JRNIAT', '', '', '', '1', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://localhost/github/amitJoshi-iiagroup/iiagroup.co.in/echronpanel/images/img-lib/15979931720.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<h2>JRNIAT-JRN INSTITUTE OF AVIATION TECHNOLOGY</h2>\n\n<p>JRN Institute of Aviation Technology, New Delhi is one of the most prestigious institute in India, which is approved by Director General Of Civil Aviation, Govt. of India for three years course in Aircraft Maintenance Engineering. It is widely recognized for its progressive approach and commitment towards excellence.</p>\n\n<p>Distinction and training are the twin hallmarks of our philosophy, our mission is to meet the need for employment &amp; professional advancement in highly sophisticated and latest generation technology with rapidly growing field of aviation industry. The special character of the JRNIAT has shaped the destinies of each individual entering its folds.</p>\n\n<p>FOUNDATION</p>\n\n<p>JRN Institute of Aviation Technology was inaugurated on 28th July 2005. Within a very short span of 3 years it shifted to its new campus. The well planned building with beautiful architecture houses well lit &amp; ventilated class rooms having OHP and LCD Projector &amp; laboratories in Mechanical and Avionics equipped equipped with modern electronic devices &amp; well stocked Library in its 25000 Sq. ft area. Ample space for indoor games, big canteen, spacious lobbies, huge parking spaces, complete power backup system, high speed internet has made it self suficient &amp; self contained AME institute. The five thousand Sq. ft. hanger is the most attractive feature of the Institute accommodates Lear Jet 24, Helicopter EC-120B, Bonanza A35 for practical experience of<br />\nthe students. This provides a platform to achieve their goals in their respective fields of aircraft maintenance engineering.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://localhost/github/amitJoshi-iiagroup/iiagroup.co.in/echronpanel/images/img-lib/15979931160.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<h3>PROFESSIONAL ENVIRONMENT</h3>\n\n<p>It is beneath the effervescence of its campuses, that the student of JRNIAT and the wellsprings of the professional attitude and vigor, which distinguish it from other Institutes. Students are guided to develop their abilities and talents, and discover their teaming potential to the fullest extent, which is imposed in an invigorating and competitive atmosphere, Created by excellent facilities, and exposure and guidance provided by a highly qualified experiences &amp; dedicated faculty.</p>\n\n<p>As it has been said &ldquo;It is good to have an end to Journey but it is the journey that matters at the end&rdquo;. The involvement of the JRN Institute of Aviation Technology in universal training enhancement and its endeavor to build a platform for hard working and sincere students to achieve their goals in aviation. To enhance the training sphere the institute is also extending its scope of approval in Radio &amp; navigation System, along with other licenses i.e. Heavy Aircraft, Light Aircraft, Rotary Wing Aircraft &amp; Piston Engine. So that the student gets a wider choice while opting for a AME career in Avionics Stream or in Mechanical Stream (Fixed Wing Aircraft and Rotary Wing Aircraft).</p>\n\n<h3>INFRASTRUCTURE</h3>\n\n<p>The institute&rsquo;s Avionics Lab, Airframe shop and Engine shop is worth of pride as it not only includes the latest indigenously built test equipment for checking and testing sophisticated avionics equipments but also includes item/equipments from AIRBUS series to give the student an in-depth view of items/equipments of latest aircraft. The library mirrors the current advancement<br />\nmade in the sphere of Technology &amp; Engineering. Our institute is equipped with a library having large collection of DVDs, CDs, CBTs on AME subjects and computers with Broadband Internet facilities. An enriched library is an essential requisite of an Engineering or Technical Institution. We also provide Audio-Visual training with these digital media&rsquo;s as a part of our constant<br />\nendeavor to enrich our training programme and for the better understanding of the subjects. To satiate the need of the students and to meet the latest DGCA (Director General of Civil Aviation) requirements, the Institute is equipped with the prescribed books on various stream of AME courses.</p>\n\n<p>Our classrooms are well equipped with laptops and LCD projectors for delivering lectures through power point based training notes. Our faculty members include experienced AME Engineers from Civil Aviation field and technical personnel from Indian Air force and graduate engineers. Through live experience the faculty members explain the subjects in the way it is easily<br />\nunderstood &amp; digested by the student.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://localhost/github/amitJoshi-iiagroup/iiagroup.co.in/echronpanel/images/img-lib/15979931171.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<h3>CORE OBJECTIVE</h3>\n\n<p>The core objective of our training programme is to impart more practical knowledge to the students regarding various maintenance practices/activities. That&rsquo;s why the syllabus has been designed to give equal importance to both theory and practical classes. Various personality development programmes like group discussion, seminar, have been incorporated along with training so that student not only excel in their academic career but also become a complete knowledgeable engineer at the end of the AME course. We have promised ourselves to give the best group of Aircraft Maintenance Engineers to the Civil Aviation sector to match the international standards as specified by International civil Aviation Organization.</p>\n', '40', 1, '1', '2020-10-12 13:25:22', '2020-08-21 12:26:55'),
(11, 'Bia patna', '', '', '', '1', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"localhost/github/amitJoshi-iiagroup/iiagroup.co.in/echronpanel/images/img-lib/15979939310.jpg\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://localhost/github/amitJoshi-iiagroup/iiagroup.co.in/echronpanel/images/img-lib/15979939310.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<h2>Approved by Directorate General of Civil Aviation, Government of India<br />\n&nbsp;</h2>\n\n<h3>Bharat Institute Of Aeronautics (BIA) was established in year 1981. The college is situated in premises of Jai Prakash Narayan International Airport, Patna.</h3>\n\n<p>Bharat Institute of Aeronautics (BIA), Patna is one of the primary Institutions promoting aviation awareness and moving forward towards progressive development with changing time &amp; technology. The Institute provides ICAO (International Civil Aviation Organization) standard of Aircraft Maintenance Engineering Course in one roof facility. The Institute is Approved by the Director General of Civil Aviation (DGCA), Govt. of India. The Institute is equipped with all varieties of modern technologies such as different varieties of aircraft and equipment model for understanding of dimension aspects of aircraft engineering.<br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h2>SALIENT FEATURES</h2>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"color:#606062\">Institute is equipped with two operational aircrafts.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"color:#606062\">Highly experienced and qualified faculties.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"color:#606062\">Well equipped laboratories and workshops with latest technical aid to impart practical training.</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"color:#606062\">100% ragging free environment.</span><br />\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://localhost/github/amitJoshi-iiagroup/iiagroup.co.in/echronpanel/images/img-lib/15979939430.jpg\" /></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>FACULTY</h2>\n\n<p>Bharat Institute of Aeronautics has some of the most qualified and skilled trainers who are dedicated and professionally amongst the best. Their vast experience and knowledge of the aviation industry is unmatched. Individual case study pertaining to the respective module with the use of modern training aid gives knowledge and skill development program a leading edge over their contemporaries</p>\n', '40', 1, '1', '2020-10-12 13:39:03', '2020-08-21 12:36:17'),
